cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with visual-semantic embedding models for image classification and zero-shot learning, which are primarily computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. The model proposed in the paper involves mapping images into a continuous semantic label space, which is a machine learning (cs.LG) problem. Additionally, the paper also deals with multi-label image annotation and zero-shot learning, which are multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
